UnitedHealth, Pfizer share gains lead Dow's 150-point climb

Shares of UnitedHealth and Pfizer are posting positive momentum Wednesday morning, sending the Dow Jones Industrial Average into positive territory. The Dow DJIA, +0.52% is trading 153 points, or 0.5%, higher, as shares of UnitedHealth UNH, -1.40% and Pfizer PFE, -0.48% are contributing to the blue-chip gauge's intraday rally. UnitedHealth's shares have climbed $5.08, or 1.7%, while those of Pfizer have risen $0.63, or 1.6%, combining for a roughly 39-point boost for the Dow. Also contributing significantly to the gain are Merck MRK, -0.38%, IBM IBM, +2.11%, and McDonald's MCD, +0.12%. A $1 move in any of the benchmark's 30 components results in a 6.78-point swing.